casebody.data:
UNITED EDUCATORS OF SAN FRANCISCO AFT/CFT, AFL-CIO, NEA/CTA
v.
CALIFORNIA UNEMPLOYMENT INSURANCE (SAN FRANCISCO UNIFIED SCHOOL DISTRICT) S235903 Supreme Court of California September 14, 2016

The petitions for review are granted. For purposes of briefing and oral argument, plaintiff and appellant United Educators of San Francisco AFT/CFT, AFL-CIO, NEA/CTA is deemed the petitioner in this court. (Cal. Rules of Court, rule 8.520(a)(6).)

Votes: Cantil-Sakauye, C.J., Werdegar, Chin, Liu, Cuéllar and Kruger, JJ. Corrigan, J., was absent and did not participate.
